channel.title: Two northern Ontario men honoured with Medal of Bravery
channel.description:
two northern ontario men honoured with medal of bravery
Local health officials have confirmed 14 cases of giardia lamblia, a rare stomach malady also known as "Beaver Fever" because beavers often carry the parasite that infects the stomach and intestines. The source of the illness was food served at a picnic on Poverty Hollow Road in Newtown this summer. The event was attended by a group of librarians from the Stamford campus of the ..
